{
  "texts": [
    "Anomalies were detected by a unique technique of mapping regular input into the hypersphere.",
    "However, the limitation persists when only some hosts contain standard data.",
    "Another study, FLDID (Verma et al. 2022), was suggested for securing smart manufacturing to detect cyber anomalies like DoS, DDoS, and ransomware using a hybrid deep learning model (CNN, LSTM, MLP).",
    "Models are trained locally on edge devices, preserving privacy with Paillierbased encryption during transmission.",
    "Due to the high computational cost, future work aims to optimize encryption and cluster clients to mitigate data poisoning attacks."
  ]
}